## 8. Role-Based Access Control Built In

TortureLang provides a **first-class role management system** embedded in the language runtime.

### Role Commands

```
grant viewer to student via root;        -- delegate a role
grant editor to teacher via root;        -- delegate another role
delegate viewer to assistant with teacher; -- sub-delegate
revoke editor from teacher;              -- remove delegation
assume viewer with student;              -- activate a role
trace to student;                        -- audit the delegation chain
```

### Function-Level Role Enforcement

```torture
function public callable void viewscore(readable int:32 score)
    code size 256 max stack size 128
    requires security level 1
    allowed roles viewer
{
    proceed verifyfunctionidentity();
    ...
}
```

At runtime, the VM enforces that the caller's authority chain contains a valid role that matches `allowed roles`. This provides **compiler-enforced, runtime-checked access control** without external frameworks.

