## 11. Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- CMake 4.0+
- C++23-compatible compiler (GCC 14+, Clang 18+, MSVC 19.40+)
- 45 minutes per compile (for optimal environment binding)

### Build Instructions

```bash
git clone https://github.com/LangLang03/Lang.git
cd Lang
cmake -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
cmake --build build --parallel 1  # sequential build for reproducibility
```

### Write Your First Program

Create `hello.torture` with the Hello World example above.

### Compile and Run

```bash
build/torturec check hello.torture
build/torturec compile hello.torture -o hello.tbc
build/torturevm run hello.tbc
```

### Cross-Platform Deployment

To deploy to a different platform, **recompile from source on that platform**. This is not a limitation — it is a **security requirement**.

